<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,618,1255]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,618,643]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Medium sized (
<quantity box="[476,562,619,643]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="24.0">24 mm</quantity>
for only known species) and body robust (
<figureCitation box="[1092,1197,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 140–145" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1926,1948]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,205,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[151,1435,205,1880]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 140–145. Hugelgryllacris n. gen. (H. tchancha n. comb.). 140. Habitus. 141. Frons. 142. Hind femur. 143. Left tegmina. 144–145. Female terminalia in lateral and ventral view. See the papillae on the last sternite. Figs. 141–144 redraw from Hugel 2009. Figs. 146–155." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2944927/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 140</figureCitation>
). Head globose and prominent (
<figureCitation box="[285,386,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 140–145" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1926,1948]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,205,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[151,1435,205,1880]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 140–145. Hugelgryllacris n. gen. (H. tchancha n. comb.). 140. Habitus. 141. Frons. 142. Hind femur. 143. Left tegmina. 144–145. Female terminalia in lateral and ventral view. See the papillae on the last sternite. Figs. 141–144 redraw from Hugel 2009. Figs. 146–155." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2944927/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 141</figureCitation>
), wider than pronotum, ocelli inconspicuous, fore coxa with a little developed spine; legs moderately short and robust, with four pairs of short movable ventral spines (excluding the two little apical spines) on fore and mid-tibiae, hind femora armed with medium sized spines from the middle to apex ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[1325,1423,726,751]" captionStart="FIGURES 140–145" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1926,1948]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,205,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[151,1435,205,1880]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 140–145. Hugelgryllacris n. gen. (H. tchancha n. comb.). 140. Habitus. 141. Frons. 142. Hind femur. 143. Left tegmina. 144–145. Female terminalia in lateral and ventral view. See the papillae on the last sternite. Figs. 141–144 redraw from Hugel 2009. Figs. 146–155." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2944927/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 142</figureCitation>
); wings well developed, covering the last abdominal tergites; M vein born near the R basal section (variation of the IV 
<typeStatus box="[188,236,799,823]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">type</typeStatus>
venation) (
<figureCitation box="[365,464,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 140–145" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1926,1948]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,205,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[151,1435,205,1880]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 140–145. Hugelgryllacris n. gen. (H. tchancha n. comb.). 140. Habitus. 141. Frons. 142. Hind femur. 143. Left tegmina. 144–145. Female terminalia in lateral and ventral view. See the papillae on the last sternite. Figs. 141–144 redraw from Hugel 2009. Figs. 146–155." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2944927/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 143</figureCitation>
). Penultimate sternite bearing a process on the anterior margin of the sternite, directed backwards; longer than the subgenital plate; ovipositor as long as the hind femur, smooth and with rounded tip (
<figureCitation box="[159,324,870,895]" captionStart="FIGURES 140–145" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1926,1948]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,205,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[151,1435,205,1880]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 140–145. Hugelgryllacris n. gen. (H. tchancha n. comb.). 140. Habitus. 141. Frons. 142. Hind femur. 143. Left tegmina. 144–145. Female terminalia in lateral and ventral view. See the papillae on the last sternite. Figs. 141–144 redraw from Hugel 2009. Figs. 146–155." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2944927/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Figs. 144, 145</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
